    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PAA\n1771 PA",
      "L0'211'8102\nPAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS PHOTO\nPAN AMERICAN TO RECEIVE SEVEN NEW DC-7BS\nThe new Douglas DC-7B will be the fastest plane over the\nAtlantic when placed in service by Pan American World Airways In\nJune. The 353-m1le-per-hour aircraft will provide non-stop service\nbetween New York and London and Paris.\nCarrying a full load of 71 passengers in tourist service,\nthe speedy planes will cut an hour and a half from the New York-\nParis flights. Newly-designed seats with built-in tables and\nenlarged galleys are among the improvements that will make the new\nDouglas the most comfortable plane flying the Atlantic.\n#\n#\n#\n#\n#\nPAN AMERICAN WORLD AIRWAYS\n135 East 42nd Street\nNew York 11'6-7100\nNew York\nMUrray H111"
    ],
